answers.answer:
If you have completed your studies, you should provide the following documents to enroll in a study cycle in Romania:
* Passport;
* Certificates or decisions of recognition of studies issued by the Ukrainian authorities;
* Equivalence decision issued by the CNRED (if needed);
* Diplomas that allow access to the study cycle in which you want to enroll.

answers.bResponse:
If you have completed your studies, you should provide the following documents to enroll in a study cycle in Romania:
* Passport;
* Certificates or decisions of recognition of studies issued by the Ukrainian authorities;
* Equivalence decision issued by the CNRED (if needed);
* Diplomas that allow access to the study cycle in which you want to enroll. For more details, visit https://dopomoha.ro/en/education
